  "prompt": "What are some lesser known facts about PM Narendra Modi?",
  "response": "Narendra Modi, the Prime Minister of India, is a prominent political figure, but there are several lesser-known facts about him that may not be widely recognized:\n\n1. **Early Life and Humble Beginnings**: Modi was born into a family of grocers in Vadnagar, Gujarat. He helped his father sell tea as a child and later ran his own tea stall.\n\n2. **RSS Connection**: Before entering mainstream politics, Modi was involved with the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS), a Hindu nationalist organization, from a young age. He began his training as a pracharak (campaigner) and worked his way up in the organization.\n\n3. **Chief Minister of Gujarat**: Modi served as the Chief Minister of Gujarat from 2001 to 2014. His tenure was marked by significant economic growth but also controversy, particularly regarding the 2002 Gujarat riots.\n\n4. **Personal Interests**: Modi is known for his interest in yoga and meditation. He has put a significant emphasis on promoting yoga both in India and internationally.\n\n5. **Cultural Initiatives**: Modi has been involved in various cultural initiatives, such as the \"Swachh Bharat Abhiyan\" (Clean India Campaign) and the promotion of traditional Indian arts and crafts.\n\n6. **Tech-Savvy Leader**: He is known for his use of social media as a political tool and has a significant following on platforms like Twitter and Instagram. His government has also emphasized the importance of technology in governance.\n\n7. **Literary Interests**: Modi is an avid reader and has written several books, including a book on the Indian freedom struggle titled \"Aaranayak\" and a compilation of his speeches.\n\n8. **National Awards**: In addition to political accolades, Modi has received a variety of awards for his contributions to society, including the \"Order of Abdulaziz al Saud\" by the Saudi Arabian government and other international honors.\n\n9. **Environmental Efforts**: Modi has been a proponent of solar energy and has launched initiatives aimed at promoting renewable energy in India, positioning the country as a leader in climate change efforts.\n\n10. **Culinary Skills**: He is a fan of Gujarati cuisine and enjoys cooking. His dishes often highlight traditional Indian recipes, and he has been seen preparing food during various public interactions.\n\nThese facts paint a more nuanced picture of Narendra Modi beyond his political persona and highlight his interests, background, and the initiatives he champions.",
